<div id="sub-main" >
	<div id="wiki-content-block">

	
		


<div id="infobox" class="infobox"> 
 <div class="table-responsive"> 
  <table class="wiki_table"> 
   <tbody> 
    <tr> 
     <th style="text-align: center;" colspan="2"> <h2>Greatshield Talisman</h2> </th> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td style="text-align: center;" colspan="2"><img title="Greatshield Talisman" src="/file/Elden-Ring/greatshield_talisman_talisman_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png" alt="greatshield talisman talisman elden ring wiki guide 200px" width="200" height="200"></td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td>Weight</td> 
     <td>0.9</td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td colspan="2"><img title="item_effect_icon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_18px" src="/file/Elden-Ring/item_effects_icon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_55px_18px.png" alt="item effects icon elden ring wiki guide 55px 18px" width="18" height="18">Effect 
      <div class="lineleft"> 
       <img src="/file/Elden-Ring/status_effect_85_elden_ring_wiki_guide_44px.png" alt="status effect 85 elden ring wiki guide 44px" width="20" height="20">&nbsp;Increases Guard Boost by 10% 
      </div> </td> 
    </tr> 
   </tbody> 
  </table> 
 </div> 
</div> 
<p><strong>Greatshield Talisman</strong>&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Talismans" href="/Talismans">Talisman</a> in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>.&nbsp;Greatshield Talisman&nbsp;increases Guard Boost by 10%.&nbsp;Players can use talismans&nbsp;in Elden Ring to boost a variety of <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Stats" href="/Stats" target="">Stats</a>.&nbsp;</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>Talisman depicting a knight holding a greatshield.</em><br><em>Boosts guarding ability.</em></p> 
 <p><em>The knights of Leyndell once modelled themselves after the Tree Sentinels. Their purpose is to protect that which deserves protection, and thus the shield always comes before the sword.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Greatshield Talisman Effect</h3> 
<p>Greatshield Talisman&nbsp;increases Guard Boost by 10%.</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to find Greatshield Talisman</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Found in a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Carriage" href="/Carriage">Carriage</a> chest, east of the&nbsp;<strong>Erdtree-Gazing Hill</strong> site of grace. [<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=3835&amp;lat=-101.&amp;lng=78&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA" href="/Interactive+Map?id=3835&amp;lat=-101.&amp;lng=78&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA">Map link</a>]</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring&nbsp;Greatshield Talisman Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Sell value:&nbsp;<img title="Runes" src="/file/Elden-Ring/runes-currency-elden-ring-wiki-guide-18.png" alt="runes currency elden ring wiki guide 18" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;500 <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Runes" href="/Runes">Runes</a></li> 
 <li>This talisman multiplies your Guard Boost rating by 1.1, reducing the amount of stamina that is lost when you block attacks. 
  <ul> 
   <li>Note: The value that gets multiplied is the actual Guard Boost (including decimals) rather than the display value. This result is then rounded up for stamina reduction calculations if any decimal is present.</li> 
  </ul> </li> 
 <li>This talisman does not increase damage reduction from blocking.</li> 
 <li>As of v1.04, the Guard Boost bonus from the Greatshield Talisman is smaller for <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Greatshields" href="/Greatshields" target="">Greatshields</a> that have a higher innate Guard Boost (like the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Fingerprint Stone Shield" href="/Fingerprint+Stone+Shield">Fingerprint Stone Shield</a>). This means you cannot reach 100 Guard Boost using the talisman alone.</li> 
 <li>As of now, the actual effect of the talisman is unknown, after thorough testing, it has made little to no difference and has had inconsistent results.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="row"> 
 <div class="col-sm-6"> 
