				<li id="16499347" class="cmnt-root" data="30" data-d="1647142310000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t579799/Greatshield-Talisman" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">12 Mar 2022 22:31</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16499347" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">I think the talisman gives a different amount of guard boost depending on whether you are using a greatshield or a normal shield. On a partially upgrade brass shield I had 59 guard boost and +35 from the barricade shield weapon art. I put on this talisman and was losing slivers of stamina from blocking massive hits. I upgraded the shield to get a base 60 guard boost and lost no stamina from blocking with the talisman and weapon art combo. This means it was adding a flat +5 guard boost to my medium shield. Other comments have been saying it adds +10 guard boost to there shields, but seem to be testing it with greatshields mostly. It appears to give +5 guard boost with normal shields and +10 with greatshields.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16499347" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16499347" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">2</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up">